        <name>pre_located</name>
        <qualifiedname>llext_load_param::pre_located</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Use the virtual symbol addresses from the ELF, not addresses within the memory buffer, when calculating relocation targets. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>It also means, that the application will take care to place the extension at those pre-defined addresses, so the LLEXT core doesn&apos;t have to do any allocation and copying internally. Any MMU permission adjustment will be done by the application too. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
